{
  "message": "fuzz(btree-bw-tree): fix entries_count oracle + 24 structured seeds\n\nThe fuzz harness asserted result.entries_count == 0 in the\nchain_len_before <= 1 branch, but MappingTable::consolidate_page\nwas deliberately fixed to return the real entries_count from the\nBase delta when one is present (per its own comment: \"Reporting\nentries_count here as a hard-coded zero misleads operator\ndashboards and metrics consumers\"). On a freshly consolidated\npage, chain_len drops to 1 with a non-empty Base, so the harness\nfired a spurious abort the next time consolidate_page was called.\nReproducible with input bytes [4,0,1,11,8,8,5,5,0,0,5,11,8,8,5]\n(insert one key, consolidate, consolidate again).\n\nFix: assert against the model's actual entries.len() in both\nbranches, matching the lib's contract.\n\nAdd 24 structured seeds spanning the harness's 10 opcodes:\n  * allocate_page (capacity 0 / 4 / 16 / overflow)\n  * insert / delete / lookup hit and miss\n  * split (separator removes upper-half keys)\n  * merge delta (no-op materialization)\n  * consolidate_page across chain lengths and thresholds\n  * consolidate_all with zero / matching / high thresholds\n  * scan_for_consolidation candidate enumeration\n  * invalid_page_id error paths (empty table + after allocs)\n  * long mixed-op history (40 inserts / mod-3 deletes / consolidate)\n  * full capacity-16 workload across all pages\n\nCoverage grew 33 \u2192 71 corpus entries on libFuzzer mutation post-fix.",
